The paper presents methods for k-means clustering on a stream, which involves processing data in a continuous and potentially infinite manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category, which deals with efficient algorithms and data structures for processing large datasets. Additionally, the paper focuses on providing fast responses to clustering queries, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, which deals with the development of algorithms for learning from data. The paper also mentions the use of coresets, which are summaries of data that can be used to speed up clustering algorithms, suggesting that it may belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category, which deals with the storage and retrieval of large datasets. Finally, the paper's focus on efficiency and low space usage suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories, which both deal with the development of algorithms for processing large amounts of data efficiently.
